reviews.text: Clunky old diesel trains chug through pretty countryside, lakes and gravel pits and past big old factories until you reach this relatively remote rural station. Quite a novelty in the crowded south east of England.

The platforms to this primitive railway station are wheelchair accessible. There are no stairs at this station. There are no installed cctv cameras at this station. The shelters are not rain proof and any passenger in the shelter when its raining is likely to get wet. The location of this station is difficult to get to if you are on foot. The design of the road does not favour any foot pedestrian heading towards the station as there is no continious laid out paved path to the station. This is particularly dangerous as where the road bends, and on-coming speeding vehicles which cannot be seen until last minute for any person on foot on the road.
